EmailTemplate.textOnly: - - - - Clean Clean false false false false EN-US X-NONE X-NONE Hi Wilson, Great to hear from you and welcome back to MBO! Please follow the steps below to complete your re-enrollment. - Log in to the MBO site www.mbopartners.com <http://mkto-l0128.com/track?t=c&&&&http://www.mbopartners.com?mkt_tok=2xUAKZjCVlBesV44xvOLI63NnDzUNJunttYXY52MuKVUsyIUGIalUg%3D%3D> - Click the “Enrollment” link once you are logged in - Confirm contact information - Print out I-9 at the end of the enrollment - You will sign/date section 1 and local notary will sign/date section 2 (most people visit their local bank.) Please email or fax back to MBO (we do not need an original copy.) If you use a US passport as supporting documentation I will need an image of it to comply with E-Verify (most people just take a picture with their phone and then email it to me.) - When appropriate,please send me your clients contact information (name, email, phone number) and I will reach out to get a contract in place. I checked out StateFarm in our system and we don’t have a contract with them at this time but they are a prospect of ours. It may be useful to send them this document <http://info.mbopartners.com/rs/mbo/images/MBO_Partners_Introduction.pdf> which explains what we do for organizations. - The link to my private page can be found here <http://info.mbopartners.com/advisor-info-s-conde.html> there are lots of great resources on this page and I encourage you to bookmark it. Please contact me with any questions.
